# Operations & DAX

## Four read shapes

- **`GetItem`** — one item by key — cheapest
- **`Query`** — items in **one PK** (± SK range) — the **workhorse**
- **`Scan`** — reads the **whole table**, charges for all — **almost always wrong** (→ GSI)
- **`Batch`** — ≤ 100 gets / 25 writes — saves round-trips, not capacity

**Trap:** filter expressions run **after** the read → filtered items still cost capacity.

## DAX — microsecond reads

In-memory cache for DynamoDB: **microsecond** hits, **drop-in** SDK.

- **Write-through** · item cache (5 min) + query cache (1 min) · **VPC-only, multi-AZ**
- For **read-heavy hot items**; serves eventually-consistent (not for strong reads).
